# [SIDROPS](../wg/sidrops.html)

## Summary

The SIDROPS Working Group met to discuss several key items concerning the security of internet routing. The primary focus of the session was coordinating the publication of the Autonomous System Provider Authorization (ASPA) cluster of documents, which are currently in Working Group Last Call (WGLC). Other major topics included updates on the Erik Synchronization Protocol, prioritizing local resource data alongside RPKI validation, post-quantum cryptography migration strategies, egress AS_PATH verification, Autonomous System Relationship Authorization (ASRA), relying party requirements, and data-plane measurements of RPKI propagation times.

